<BaseLayout
  title="About — Books"
  description="What books.oriz.in is and why it exists."
>
  <div class="spine-prose">
    <header class="page-head">
      <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">CATALOGUE</a> / ABOUT</p>
      <h1>About oriz · books.</h1>
    </header>

    <article class="prose">
      <p class="lede">
        <strong>Books</strong> is a flat directory of NCERT textbooks for
        India's school curriculum (Class I — XII). It is a static site —
        every page is pre-built, every download is a direct link to
        <a href="https://ncert.nic.in/">ncert.nic.in</a>. Nothing is hosted
        on this domain.
      </p>

      <h2>Why this exists</h2>
      <p>
        The official NCERT site works, but it is slow, hard to navigate, and
        its links break often. Books gives you one filter rail and one card
        grid: pick a class, pick a subject, pick a medium, click the card.
        No popups, no ads (yet), no required sign-in, no PDF interception.
      </p>

      <h2>What you get</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Full directory of NCERT textbooks with metadata.</li>
        <li>One-click download of individual chapters or the merged full-book PDF.</li>
        <li>Search across titles, subjects, chapters, and keywords (Hindi and English).</li>
        <li>Optional sign-in — shared with the rest of <a href="https://oriz.in/">oriz</a> — to bookmark books.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Where the data comes from</h2>
      <p>
        The catalogue is scraped from <code>ncert.nic.in</code> by a Playwright
        pipeline in this repo's <code>tools/</code> folder, normalised into
        <code>public/data/metadata/books.json</code>, and committed back to git.
        Every page on this site is rebuilt from that JSON.
      </p>

      <h2>oriz family</h2>
      <p>
        Books is one of eleven sites in the
        <a href="https://oriz.in/">oriz</a> family. Use the family menu in
        the footer to jump between them.
      </p>

      <h2>Source code</h2>
      <p>
        MIT-licensed, hosted at
        <a href="https://github.com/chirag127/oriz-books">github.com/chirag127/oriz-books</a>.
        Issues and PRs welcome.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
